<subSubSection id="29E07ED710CB5CE52DD674FE5D8D7106" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="786466BF8227CDA8F3363D19CBB76FF4" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" type="mainText">Comments. The combination of O. balzani-group mandibles, two pairs of setae on the promesonotum, and flattened setae on the scape uniquely characterize this distinctive species. New measurements for the worker are HW 0.51-0.57, HL 0.47-0.53, CI 106-108 (n=4). The queen is reported with measurements HW 0.58, HL 0.55, CI 105 (Perrault, 1988).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
